 {
  "id": "tier0-ugly-three-desks-reverse_mods",
  "arm": "tier0",
  "raw": "Neither sentence is grammatically correct or natural in English because \"three\" is a plural number and cannot be preceded by the singular article \"a\" or \"an\" in this context. \n\nHowever, if forced to choose which one is closer to standard English word order (ignoring the incorrect article):\n\n* \"ugly three desks\" (A) is incorrect because opinion adjectives (\"ugly\") should not come before a specific cardinal number (\"three\").\n* \"three ugly desks\" is the correct natural order (Number + Opinion + Noun). \n\nIf the article \"a\" in **B** is a typo for \"the\" (i.e., \"She bought the three ugly desks\"), then B represents the correct word order. \n\nIf you must choose strictly between the two options as written, **B** is closer to the correct adjective order, but both are highly unnatural due to the article \"a/an\".",
